I would argue there are: calling refugees people that don't fit the definition of a refugee, calling annexations made by Hungary as "improvements" and denying there is a Hungarian bias? There's more, but I joined the discussion, I believe we can discuss this there.

My contribution had more than just those, so even if you were right about those inaccuracies, your removal of the whole contribution because of those is not justified. Yes, the Austrians did not accept the Hungarian demands because they wanted it, they were forced to by the Hungarian protests, you'd like to use an alternative word? The Romanians were second-class citizens, they didn't had the same rights as the other 3 nations. The summary is a duplicate by definition so your point is invalid.
not OR. This is your opinion, I've seen Wikipedia articles with way longer leads and it wasn't a bad thing.

Forgot to add some parts from L'grand Anonim. Added a paragraph explaining the 1940-1941 difference. The reason "refugee" was used in this case: a refugee is someone who leaves either by force or because he is not safe there (ethnic cleansing or war); where as leaving willingly is simply relocation.
manually restored L'grand Anonim 's edits with small adjustments, they removed NPOV violations and no explicit reason was given for their removal.
no, what? I'm not against discussing on the talk page, but you removed the whole contribution without any reasoning, so there's nothing for me to say on the talk page.
what inaccuracies? I know, it's a summary, I didn't post all statistics, only the earliest.

what exactly do you want me say on the talk page? read the contribution before deleting it, I did not make any pro and contra arguments, I merely presented more the theories, so your criticism is invalid. Besides, there was more to my contribution, so your removal of the whole contribution because of that is not justified.
